76561198093427784,Recommended,444670,25993112,"Posted: 11 October, 2016",all,Ominous_Paladin,"Early Access review:  Will edit as updates come out.TLDR:  Currently a fun single player as well as couch co-op timekiller with a reasonable price tag.Bored and reading comments version: Super Impossible Road or SIR as the devs and I call it, is a little idea with big potential.Current Cons:  Limited to 3 roads and only a couple songs, online multiplayer and career are not currently in game.Whether the idea to make a racing game about cheating was an accident or a stroke of genuis remains a mystery.  What I do know is that it's freaking fun.  I was the kid no one liked to play Mario Kart with becasue I always focused on the chincy spots to use boosts and cut across as much track as possible.  Now its not just an exploit, its the principal mechanic.Falling off the track and landing 50 feet ahead may not sound like much, but when you get 5 seconds of freefall that refreshes every time you so much as graze the track, magic can happen.  Granted this is a curse as much as it is a blessing.  Without passing through gates to progress your respawn point, an incredible run ruined by one bad bounce can send you back to the starting line and irredemably far behind.  That's just the thing too, bouncing can and will happpen, and mastering it can be tricky.  Sometimes you bounce straight up and time out just hovering there, other times you get pitched impossibly far to the side where the road simply isn't.Then there's the tension, and feeling of panic.  Much like hearing the warning of Mario Kart's blue shell which puts your blood on ice, seeing an opponent fall ahead of you and skip 30 gates is terrifying.  Suddenly your killer lead has evaporated and you need to start getting risky to catch up.  You take jumps where you normally wouldn't, you expend your boost trying to keep up only to blackout and respawn.  Disheartened you look at your position and realize it still says 1st.  This is a frequent occurence, just because they passed you, doesn't mean they're ahead of you.Couch co-op gets competitive as hell cause you can see when your friends are taking jumps and you start reading their path to see if they can catch you.  Races are short enough too, unless you dial up the distance and complexity of the course so rotation of players usually isn't an issue.  If you don't have local friends, beating thr AI is plenty of fun, and there's a survival mode with leaderboards that are frankly insane.When online multi happens along with the career, this game is going to become huge, at least I hope.  A dedicated dev with a great idea, I'd hate to see it fall flat.All this is bundled with a sweet soundtrack and stunning visuals."
