76561198097632017,Recommended,444670,33901961,Posted: 30 July,all,Suntrooper,"I only play this game 4player-splitscreen and it really surprised us! It is totally addictive, and you only need a few rounds to get the hang of it. Yes, it is basically a racing game, but we realized that the racing game fans in our group did not have a huge advantage, which is good. Actually, everyone of us won some rounds and that's got to do with some key features:First, all tracks are random generated, which is necessary for this game, since you can't lean any track. Second, the idea is to take shortcuts wherever you can, because it is much faster than to stay on the road. This is a concept of risk an reward... sometimes you are 4th and go for it, make that awesome huge shortcut just before your screen fades and are back in the picture. On the other hand you can be first and afraid of losing time risking a shortcut and not making it to the road again... so the game balances itself. Sure, you get a good feeling for where to take shortcuts and get better doing it, but since the tracks are always random generated, everbody has good rounds as well as bad rounds where nothing you try seems to  work.The current content is enough to enjoy maybe half an hour to an hour at a time and to keep us coming back. I really would like to see more parts to customize your ball, maybe some additional environment. It's still early access, though, so there might be coming more.At least - and I can't say that for a lot of EAccess titles - this game looks awesome and gameplay is polished and flawless. I think it is a really addictive and fun 4-player game, especially as we didn't expect it to be that good!"
